## Post Content

[Everyone's asking me: "How do I measure whether AI is recommending my brand?"

Honest answer: Nobody has cracked this yet. And if someone's selling you a clean dashboard tracking visibility across ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Google AI Mode? That's a best guess dressed up as a metric.

The old SEO playbook doesn't transfer. The surface isn't finite. The rankings aren't stable. The journey isn't observable.

So I built something different, the Funnel Query Pathway. A framework borrowed from macroeconomics, not SEO.

The key insight for entrepreneurs: start at the bottom of the funnel.

Pick your most profitable customer at the moment they're ready to buy. Write the exact query they'd type with your brand name in it. That's your conversion node. Then project upward — the evaluation questions, the awareness questions — until you have a 50–60 query tree mapping your ideal customer's full journey.

Unlike keyword research, you're not asking what people actually type. You're asking what your ideal cohort would ask given a specific intent. Subtle shift. Huge implications.

That one tree does three jobs:

Strategy — know exactly what content to create
Measurement — run it monthly across every AI engine
Analysis — spot gaps, track momentum, adjust

Start with one. One cohort, one intent, one buying moment. The brands building this discipline now are the ones AI will recommend by name in three years.
The ones waiting for a perfect dashboard will still be waiting.

If you're an entrepreneur who sells and you want AI to recommend your brand to the right people at the right moment, this is the methodology to start with today. Read now!
